{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:52:35.318Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"text","text":"    priority: \"medium\",\n    status: \"resolved\",\n    client_id: \"client-00","accumulated":"I will outline our internal design plan before editing any source code. This aligns with the UI Quality Constitution and guarantees a precise and compliant implementation of the Support Ticket CRUD APIs.\n\n### Design Plan: MVP Support Ticket CRUD APIs\n\n#### 1. Page or Section Narrative\nThe Support Ticket APIs form the secure communication conduit (Sovereign Security Tunnel) between sandboxed client environments and GFF AI Platform Operators. To support auditability, absolute clarity, and high-security compliance, every API transaction must validate the client's role boundaries, execute rigorous input filtering, and protect physical data sovereignty.\n\n#### 2. Visual Metaphor\nA cryptographic transport tunnel. This API mimics a hardware-locked socket where commands are validated with cryptographic tokens, roles are securely mapped, and trace logs are filtered sequentially without data leakage outside the client boundary.\n\n#### 3. Layout/Architecture Strategy (Backend API)\nThe APIs will be built as modular Next.js Route Handlers (`app/api/v1/support/route.ts` and sub-routes under `app/api/v1/support/[id]/`). \n* `/api/v1/support` will support `GET` (list with filters) and `POST` (create ticket with automatic server-side field assignment).\n* `/api/v1/support/[id]` will support `GET` (by ID) and `PATCH` (generic updates, status changes, assignments, or comments).\n* Dedicated endpoint paths like `/api/v1/support/[id]/status`, `/api/v1/support/[id]/assign`, and `/api/v1/support/[id]/comments` will also be exposed for high modularity.\n* Filters will include: `status`, `priority`, `category`, `client_id`, `project_id`, `assigned_to`, and generic `search` query.\n\n#### 4. Interaction Strategy\nAll endpoints check authentication via the existing `Bearer` token structure from `lib/api-auth.ts`.\n* **RBAC Enforcement**:\n  - Administrators/Operators (`gff_admin`) can view, filter, assign, comment on, and modify all tickets.\n  - Clients can only view, filter, comment on, and modify tickets belonging to their own `client_id`. They can only create tickets bound to their own `client_id`.\n* **Backend Validation Checks**:\n  - Inputs (like title, description, category, priority, status) are strictly checked for types, emptiness, and validity.\n  - Project relationships (`project_id`) are validated to ensure they exist and belong to the correct client boundary.\n\n#### 5. Mobile Strategy\nNot directly applicable for JSON APIs, but we will return clean, expressive JSON responses with proper HTTP status codes (`200 OK`, `201 Created`, `400 Bad Request`, `401 Unauthorized`, `403 Forbidden`, `404 Not Found`) and descriptive error messages to ensure excellent developer experience and clean mobile frontend display.\n\n#### 6. Files to Change\n* `lib/api-auth.ts`: Append the `ApiSupportTicket`, `ApiSupportTicketComment` interfaces, standard seeds, mock database structures, and generator/filter helper functions.\n* Create `app/api/v1/support/route.ts`: Handler for ticket listing (GET) and creation (POST).\n* Create `app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.ts`: Handler for fetching (GET) and updating/assigning/commenting/status updates (PATCH).\n* Create `app/api/v1/support/[id]/status/route.ts`: Explicit PATCH route for ticket status.\n* Create `app/api/v1/support/[id]/assign/route.ts`: Explicit PATCH route for ticket assignment.\n* Create `app/api/v1/support/[id]/comments/route.ts`: Explicit POST route for adding replies/comments.\n\n#### 7. Files Not to Touch\n* Do not modify the approved landing page or GFF AI tool files (e.g. `app/page.tsx`, `components/PublicRoutePage.tsx`, etc.).\n* Do not alter other core routes unless necessary.\n\n---\n\nLet's first edit `lib/api-auth.ts` to add the necessary interfaces, seed data, and helper functions. Let's do a quick read of the end of `lib/api-auth.ts` to see what we'll be replacing or appending. We saw that it ended on line 524 with `getNextInvoiceId()`. We can append our new code cleanly.\n\nLet's structure the mock support tickets data perfectly.\nLet's see:\n```typescript\nexport interface ApiSupportTicketComment {\n  id: string;\n  sender: string;\n  text: string;\n  timestamp: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ApiSupportTicket {\n  id: string;\n  title: string;\n  description: string;\n  category: string;\n  priority: \"low\" | \"medium\" | \"high\" | \"critical\";\n  status: \"open\" | \"in_progress\" | \"resolved\" | \"closed\";\n  client_id: string;\n  project_id: string | null;\n  assigned_to: string | null;\n  created_by: string; // email address\n  createdAt: string;\n  lastUpdated: string;\n  replies: ApiSupportTicketComment[];\n}\n```\n\nWait, what are the exact categories that can be used? The list is `\"Project Delivery\" | \"AI Operations\" | \"Billing\" | \"Documents\" | \"Access\" | \"Governance\" | \"General\"`. Let's support any of these categories.\nLet's draft the default seed tickets:\n```typescript\nexport const DEFAULT_API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS: Record<string, ApiSupportTicket> = {\n  \"SLA-TKT-9912\": {\n    id: \"SLA-TKT-9912\",\n    title: \"Secure HSM Key Rotation Interlock Delayed\",\n    description: \"Enclave hardware is reporting socket timeout while performing automatic HSM roll-key rotation with Sovereign Core Sandbox 02. Expected timeout in 45 minutes.\",\n    category: \"AI Operations\",\n    priority: \"critical\",\n    status: \"open\",\n    client_id: \"client-001\",\n    project_id: \"proj-001\",\n    assigned_to: \"s.vance@governance.gff.ai\",\n    created_by: \"a.mercer@apex-sovereign.gff.ai\",\n    createdAt: \"2026-06-27T10:15:00Z\",\n    lastUpdated: \"2026-06-27T10:25:00Z\",\n    replies: [\n      {\n        id: \"rep-001\",\n        sender: \"Alexander Mercer\",\n        text: \"Initiated automated rotation but the ledger remains uncommitted. Telemetry is fully active.\",\n        timestamp: \"2026-06-27T10:15:00Z\"\n      },\n      {\n        id: \"rep-002\",\n        sender: \"Dr. Sarah Vance (Admin)\",\n        text: \"Analyzing cryptographic enclave stream. Standby, we will manually sign the handshake bypass if needed.\",\n        timestamp: \"2026-06-27T10:25:00Z\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"SLA-TKT-9801\": {\n    id: \"SLA-TKT-9801\",\n    title: \"Thread Load Allocation Exceeding Normal Boundaries\",\n    description: \"Node MED-CLINIC-H9 CPU utilization hit 94.5% during diagnostic prompt scan lifecycle. Requesting auto-scaling validation check.\",\n    category: \"AI Operations\",\n    priority: \"high\",\n    status: \"in_progress\",\n    client_id: \"client-002\",\n    project_id: \"proj-002\",\n    assigned_to: \"s.vance@governance.gff.ai\",\n    created_by: \"e.carter@global-retail.gff.ai\",\n    createdAt: \"2026-06-27T07:18:00Z\",\n    lastUpdated: \"2026-06-27T07:22:00Z\",\n    replies: [\n      {\n        id: \"rep-003\",\n        sender: \"Evelyn Carter\",\n        text: \"The threat mapping thread is locked in an infinite evaluation state on local SGX enclave.\",\n        timestamp: \"2026-06-27T07:18:00Z\"\n      },\n      {\n        id: \"rep-004\",\n        sender: \"Security Bot\",\n        text: \"Auto-scan activated. Sandboxed namespace isolated. No breach or policy leakage detected.\",\n        timestamp: \"2026-06-27T07:22:00Z\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"SLA-TKT-9450\": {\n    id: \"SLA-TKT-9450\",\n    title: \"SOC2 Compliance Report Signoff Complete\",\n    description: \"Audit check complete on all active sandbox namespaces. No policy violations detected across 10,000 epoch transactions.\",\n    category: \"Governance\",\n    priority: \"medium\",\n    status: \"resolved\",\n    client_id: \"client-00"}}
