{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:53:14.118Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining API Route Handlers**\n\nI'm now diving into the implementation of the `/api/v1/support` route handlers. Currently, my focus is on a modular approach, creating handlers one by one. The first one will be `/api/v1/support/route.ts`. I'm starting to flesh out its responsibilities.\n\n\n**Analyzing Ticket Listing Logic**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the logic for the `GET` route to list tickets. Specifically, I'm verifying authentication by examining our current methods. I want to make sure the JWT decoding and user retrieval are up to par. I'm focusing on the `getAuthCaller` function, specifically by inspecting the import path. I've switched to a root import: `import { ... } from \"@/lib/api-auth\"`. I've also identified key roles permitted to list the tickets: Admin/support roles and Client roles.\n\n\n**Implementing Ticket Filtering**\n\nI'm now clarifying the filtering rules for listing tickets, particularly focusing on access based on user roles and provided filters. If the caller is an admin, I'm allowing them to view all tickets, and they can filter any way they like. For non-admins, I'm extracting their `client_id` from their association to match tickets. I'm also planning to return a 403 error if a non-admin attempts to filter by a different client ID, just like the project and invoice routes. Finally, I've identified the filters to implement: status, priority, category, client_id, project_id, and assigned_to, in addition to a search term.\n\n\n**Defining Ticket Filtering Logic**\n\nI'm now building out the filtering mechanism. I'm focusing on the different filter parameters: `assigned_to` and `search`. I'm going to implement case-insensitive matching for filters such as `status`, `priority`, and `category`. Exact matching will be used for `client_id` and `project_id`, the latter considering its nullable nature. The search query will scan across `title`, `description`, `category`, and `id`. I'm starting to think about data validation and security to ensure this works well.\n\nI'm now investigating the `POST` request for ticket creation. It's becoming clear that clients can create and view tickets linked to their own `client_id`. Admins, too, are able to create tickets. As a security measure, if the caller isn't an admin, I'll validate that the ticket's `client_id` matches the caller's. A 403 will be returned if there's a mismatch.\n\n\n**Validating Ticket Creation**\n\nI'm now determining the validation rules and handling logic for ticket creation via the `POST` request. I've established that client users must have their `client_id` validated against their own and that admins can define any valid `client_id`. I'm starting to build a validation list: the required fields, such as `title`, `description`, `category`, and `priority`, are all required strings. The `status` field defaults to `\"open\"` and its valid values are defined.\n\n\n**Defining Ticket Payload**\n\nI'm now nailing down the ticket payload details for creation. I've focused on `client_id`, `project_id`, `assigned_to`, and `created_by`, including default values and validation requirements. The optional `project_id` needs type checking and existing project validation, and `assigned_to` can be a string or null. The `created_by` defaults to the authenticated caller's email. I will keep the initial `replies` array empty.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:53:14.120Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"tq2xljku","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/api/v1/support/route.ts","new_text":"import { NextResponse } from \"next/server\";\nimport { \n  API_MOCK_USERS, \n  API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS, \n  getNextSupportTicketId, \n  verifyJwt, \n  MockUserDbEntry, \n  getClientIdFromAssociation,\n  ApiSupportTicket\n} from \"@/lib/api-auth\";\n\nexport const runtime = \"nodejs\";\n\nfunction getAuthCaller(req: Request) {\n  const auth = req.headers.get(\"authorization\");\n  if (!auth?.startsWith(\"Bearer \")) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Missing/malformed Authorization header.\" };\n  }\n  const decoded = verifyJwt(auth.substring(7));\n  if (!decoded?.email) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Invalid/expired access token.\" };\n  }\n  const user = (API_MOCK_USERS as Record<string, MockUserDbEntry>)[decoded.email.toLowerCase().trim()];\n  if (!user) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Authorized user not found.\" };\n  }\n  if (user.status === \"inactive\") {\n    return { status: 403, error: \"Forbidden\", msg: \"This account is inactive.\" };\n  }\n  return { caller: user };\n}\n\nexport async function GET(req: Request) {\n  try {\n    const auth = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (\"status\" in auth) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: auth.error, message: auth.msg }, { status: auth.status });\n    }\n    const { caller } = auth;\n\n    const { searchParams } = new URL(req.url);\n    const statusFilter = searchParams.get(\"status\");\n    const priorityFilter = searchParams.get(\"priority\");\n    const categoryFilter = searchParams.get(\"category\");\n    const clientIdFilter = searchParams.get(\"client_id\");\n    const projectIdFilter = searchParams.get(\"project_id\");\n    const assignedToFilter = searchParams.get(\"assigned_to\");\n    const searchQuery = searchParams.get(\"search\");\n\n    let tickets = Object.values(API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS) as ApiSupportTicket[];\n\n    // RBAC logic\n    // Admin/support roles can manage all tickets.\n    // Client roles can view their own client tickets.\n    if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\") {\n      const callerClientId = getClientIdFromAssociation(caller.clientAssociation);\n      tickets = tickets.filter(t => t.client_id === callerClientId);\n\n      // Enforce client boundary\n      if (clientIdFilter && clientIdFilter !== callerClientId) {\n        return NextResponse.json(\n          { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Access denied to requested client's tickets.\" },\n          { status: 403 }\n        );\n      }\n    } else {\n      // Admin filters\n      if (clientIdFilter) {\n        tickets = tickets.filter(t => t.client_id === clientIdFilter);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Apply filters\n    if (statusFilter) {\n      const q = statusFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      tickets = tickets.filter(t => t.status.toLowerCase() === q);\n    }\n    if (priorityFilter) {\n      const q = priorityFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      tickets = tickets.filter(t => t.priority.toLowerCase() === q);\n    }\n    if (categoryFilter) {\n      const q = categoryFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      tickets = tickets.filter(t => t.category.toLowerCase().includes(q));\n    }\n    if (projectIdFilter) {\n      const q = projectIdFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      if (q === \"null\" || q === \"none\") {\n        tickets = tickets.filter(t => t.project_id === null || t.project_id === \"\");\n      } else {\n        tickets = tickets.filter(t => t.project_id && t.project_id.toLowerCase() === q);\n      }\n    }\n    if (assignedToFilter) {\n      const q = assignedToFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      if (q === \"null\" || q === \"unassigned\") {\n        tickets = tickets.filter(t => t.assigned_to === null);\n      } else {\n        tickets = tickets.filter(t => t.assigned_to && t.assigned_to.toLowerCase().includes(q));\n      }\n    }\n    if (searchQuery) {\n      const q = searchQuery.toLowerCase().trim();\n      tickets = tickets.filter(t => \n        t.title.toLowerCase().includes(q) || \n        t.description.toLowerCase().includes(q) || \n        t.category.toLowerCase().includes(q) ||\n        t.id.toLowerCase().includes(q)\n      );\n    }\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, tickets });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function POST(req: Request) {\n  try {\n    const auth = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (\"status\" in auth) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: auth.error, message: auth.msg }, { status: auth.status });\n    }\n    const { caller } = auth;\n\n    const body = await req.json().catch(() => null);\n    if (!body) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid JSON body.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const { title, description, category, priority, status, client_id, project_id, assigned_to } = body;\n\n    // Backend validation checks\n    if (!title || typeof title !== \"string\" || !title.trim()) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Missing or invalid 'title' field.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    if (!description || typeof description !== \"string\" || !description.trim()) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Missing or invalid 'description' field.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    if (!category || typeof category !== \"string\" || !category.trim()) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Missing or invalid 'category' field.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const validPriorities = [\"low\", \"medium\", \"high\", \"critical\"];\n    if (!priority || typeof priority !== \"string\" || !validPriorities.includes(priority.toLowerCase().trim())) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Priority must be low, medium, high, or critical.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const validStatuses = [\"open\", \"in_progress\", \"resolved\", \"closed\"];\n    const finalStatus = status ? status.toLowerCase().trim() : \"open\";\n    if (status && !validStatuses.includes(finalStatus)) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid status value specified.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    // Determine client_id and execute boundaries check\n    let finalClientId = client_id;\n    if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\") {\n      const callerClientId = getClientIdFromAssociation(caller.clientAssociation);\n      if (client_id && client_id !== callerClientId) {\n        return NextResponse.json(\n          { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Cannot create support tickets for another client organization.\" },\n          { status: 403 }\n        );\n      }\n      finalClientId = callerClientId;\n    } else {\n      // Admin must provide client_id if not deducible\n      if (!finalClientId || typeof finalClientId !== \"string\" || !finalClientId.trim()) {\n        return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Administrators must specify a valid 'client_id' field.\" }, { status: 400 });\n      }\n    }\n\n    const validClients = [\"client-001\", \"client-002\", \"client-003\", \"client-004\"];\n    if (!validClients.includes(finalClientId)) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid client_id specified.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const newTicketId = getNextSupportTicketId();\n    const nowStr = new Date().toISOString();\n\n    const newTicket: ApiSupportTicket = {\n      id: newTicketId,\n      title: title.trim(),\n      description: description.trim(),\n      category: category.trim(),\n      priority: priority.toLowerCase().trim() as ApiSupportTicket[\"priority\"],\n      status: finalStatus as ApiSupportTicket[\"status\"],\n      client_id: finalClientId,\n      project_id: project_id || null,\n      assigned_to: assigned_to || null,\n      created_by: caller.email,\n      createdAt: nowStr,\n      lastUpdated: nowStr,\n      replies: []\n    };\n\n    (API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS as Record<string, ApiSupportTicket>)[newTicketId] = newTicket;\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, ticket: newTicket }, { status: 201 });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n"}}}
