{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:53:47.295Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Confirming Route Parameter Pattern**\n\nI've confirmed Next.js 16/App Router utilizes `const { id } = await params;`, validating the asynchronous Promise nature of parameters. This confirms adherence to current best practices, and I'm keen to ensure our routes follow this convention exactly.\n\n\n**Defining Access Permissions**\n\nI'm now focusing on user roles and access control for the ticket system. It seems that admins and support have blanket access, while clients are restricted to their own tickets. I'm clarifying the PATCH status endpoint permissions; clients should likely be able to close/resolve, but admins should have wider management control. I am considering adding a comment feature, though I still need to evaluate its complexity.\n\n\n**Clarifying User Permissions**\n\nI'm now nailing down the precise access controls. I've decided to forbid clients from assigning tickets, throwing a 403 error. Clients will be able to update their own tickets with restrictions, such as not altering the assigned user. Admins and support roles are granted full modification access. I'll need to define precisely which fields clients can modify.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:53:47.298Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"rm10nnx8","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.ts","new_text":"import { NextResponse } from \"next/server\";\nimport { \n  API_MOCK_USERS, API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS, verifyJwt, \n  MockUserDbEntry, ApiSupportTicket, getClientIdFromAssociation \n} from \"@/lib/api-auth\";\n\nexport const runtime = \"nodejs\";\n\nfunction getAuthCaller(req: Request) {\n  const auth = req.headers.get(\"authorization\");\n  if (!auth?.startsWith(\"Bearer \")) return null;\n  const decoded = verifyJwt(auth.substring(7));\n  if (!decoded?.email) return null;\n  const user = (API_MOCK_USERS as Record<string, MockUserDbEntry>)[decoded.email.toLowerCase().trim()];\n  return user && user.status !== \"inactive\" ? user : null;\n}\n\nexport async function GET(req: Request, { params }: { params: any }) {\n  try {\n    const caller = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (!caller) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Unauthorized\" }, { status: 401 });\n    const { id } = await params;\n    const ticket = (API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS as Record<string, ApiSupportTicket>)[id];\n    if (!ticket) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Not Found\" }, { status: 404 });\n\n    if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\") {\n      const cid = getClientIdFromAssociation(caller.clientAssociation);\n      if (ticket.client_id !== cid) {\n        return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Access denied.\" }, { status: 403 });\n      }\n    }\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, ticket });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function PATCH(req: Request, { params }: { params: any }) {\n  try {\n    const caller = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (!caller) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Unauthorized\" }, { status: 401 });\n    const { id } = await params;\n    const ticket = (API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS as Record<string, ApiSupportTicket>)[id];\n    if (!ticket) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Not Found\" }, { status: 404 });\n\n    const isAdmin = caller.role === \"gff_admin\";\n    const cid = getClientIdFromAssociation(caller.clientAssociation);\n\n    if (!isAdmin && ticket.client_id !== cid) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Access denied.\" }, { status: 403 });\n    }\n\n    const b = await req.json().catch(() => null);\n    if (!b) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid JSON\" }, { status: 400 });\n\n    const { title, description, category, priority, status, assigned_to, comment, reply } = b;\n\n    // RBAC validation: only admin can change assigned_to\n    if (assigned_to !== undefined && !isAdmin) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Only administrators can assign tickets.\" }, { status: 403 });\n    }\n\n    if (title !== undefined) {\n      if (typeof title !== \"string\" || !title.trim()) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid title\" }, { status: 400 });\n      ticket.title = title.trim();\n    }\n\n    if (description !== undefined) {\n      if (typeof description !== \"string\" || !description.trim()) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid description\" }, { status: 400 });\n      ticket.description = description.trim();\n    }\n\n    if (category !== undefined) {\n      if (typeof category !== \"string\" || !category.trim()) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid category\" }, { status: 400 });\n      ticket.category = category.trim();\n    }\n\n    if (priority !== undefined) {\n      const valP = [\"low\", \"medium\", \"high\", \"critical\"];\n      if (typeof priority !== \"string\" || !valP.includes(priority.toLowerCase().trim())) {\n        return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid priority\" }, { status: 400 });\n      }\n      ticket.priority = priority.toLowerCase().trim() as ApiSupportTicket[\"priority\"];\n    }\n\n    if (status !== undefined) {\n      const valS = [\"open\", \"in_progress\", \"resolved\", \"closed\"];\n      if (typeof status !== \"string\" || !valS.includes(status.toLowerCase().trim())) {\n        return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid status\" }, { status: 400 });\n      }\n      ticket.status = status.toLowerCase().trim() as ApiSupportTicket[\"status\"];\n    }\n\n    if (assigned_to !== undefined) {\n      ticket.assigned_to = assigned_to ? String(assigned_to).trim() : null;\n    }\n\n    // Append simple comment/reply if provided\n    const commentData = comment || reply;\n    if (commentData) {\n      const text = typeof commentData === \"string\" ? commentData : (commentData.text || commentData.reply);\n      if (text && typeof text === \"string\" && text.trim()) {\n        ticket.replies.push({\n          id: `rep-${Math.floor(1000 + Math.random() * 9000)}`,\n          sender: isAdmin ? `${caller.name} (Admin)` : caller.name,\n          text: text.trim(),\n          timestamp: new Date().toISOString()\n        });\n      }\n    }\n\n    ticket.lastUpdated = new Date().toISOString();\n    (API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS as Record<string, ApiSupportTicket>)[id] = ticket;\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, ticket });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n"}}}
