{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:53:57.024Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining API Endpoints**\n\nI've successfully created a flawless setup! My focus now shifts to crafting specific sub-endpoints for our API. I'm prioritizing `PATCH` methods for status updates and assignments, focusing on resources like `/api/v1/support/[id]/status` and `/api/v1/support/[id]/assign`. I am also working on `POST` for the last endpoint.\n\n\n**Adding Comment Endpoints**\n\nNow, I'm integrating the `/comments` endpoint for enhanced functionality, fully treating it as a first-class citizen. I am building the corresponding route file to be the pinnacle of elegance: `/app/api/v1/support/[id]/comments/route.ts`. The implementation will be concise. The status route file is being worked on.\n\n\n**Refining Patch Logic**\n\nI am currently immersed in refining the PATCH method's logic, specifically for status updates, and checking authorizations. I am focused on detailed error handling now, including implementing a robust system for handling unauthorized requests and ensuring that only authorized users or administrators can modify ticket statuses. I'm prioritizing efficient JSON parsing and validating incoming data against an allowed set of statuses to minimize potential issues.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:53:57.026Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"3nv34ksa","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/api/v1/support/[id]/status/route.ts","new_text":"import { NextResponse } from \"next/server\";\nimport { \n  API_MOCK_USERS, API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS, verifyJwt, \n  MockUserDbEntry, ApiSupportTicket, getClientIdFromAssociation \n} from \"@/lib/api-auth\";\n\nexport const runtime = \"nodejs\";\n\nfunction getAuthCaller(req: Request) {\n  const auth = req.headers.get(\"authorization\");\n  if (!auth?.startsWith(\"Bearer \")) return null;\n  const decoded = verifyJwt(auth.substring(7));\n  if (!decoded?.email) return null;\n  const user = (API_MOCK_USERS as Record<string, MockUserDbEntry>)[decoded.email.toLowerCase().trim()];\n  return user && user.status !== \"inactive\" ? user : null;\n}\n\nexport async function PATCH(req: Request, { params }: { params: any }) {\n  try {\n    const caller = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (!caller) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Unauthorized\" }, { status: 401 });\n    const { id } = await params;\n    const ticket = (API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS as Record<string, ApiSupportTicket>)[id];\n    if (!ticket) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Not Found\" }, { status: 404 });\n\n    const isAdmin = caller.role === \"gff_admin\";\n    if (!isAdmin && ticket.client_id !== getClientIdFromAssociation(caller.clientAssociation)) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Access denied.\" }, { status: 403 });\n    }\n\n    const b = await req.json().catch(() => null);\n    if (!b || typeof b.status !== \"string\") {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid status value.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const valS = [\"open\", \"in_progress\", \"resolved\", \"closed\"];\n    const status = b.status.toLowerCase().trim();\n    if (!valS.includes(status)) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid status\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    ticket.status = status as ApiSupportTicket[\"status\"];\n    ticket.lastUpdated = new Date().toISOString();\n    (API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS as Record<string, ApiSupportTicket>)[id] = ticket;\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, ticket });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n"}}}
