{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:54:05.531Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Developing Assignment API**\n\nI'm currently focused on constructing the route handler for assigning support tickets. I've begun by importing the necessary modules, like NextResponse from next/server, along with mock data and utility functions such as verifyJwt and getClientIdFromAssociation. Now I will write the function that does the assigning, I will ensure this implementation is secure and robust for this crucial API endpoint.\n\n\n**Implementing Authentication Layer**\n\nI've just added the authentication layer to the assignment function. I'm checking the 'authorization' header for a Bearer token, verifying it using `verifyJwt`, and retrieving the user details. I'm verifying the user is active, using mock data from `API_MOCK_USERS`, and returning an unauthorized response if needed. I'm also now planning to integrate this auth logic into the update function.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:54:05.534Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"uc2nalw8","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/api/v1/support/[id]/assign/route.ts","new_text":"import { NextResponse } from \"next/server\";\nimport { \n  API_MOCK_USERS, API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS, verifyJwt, \n  MockUserDbEntry, ApiSupportTicket \n} from \"@/lib/api-auth\";\n\nexport const runtime = \"nodejs\";\n\nfunction getAuthCaller(req: Request) {\n  const auth = req.headers.get(\"authorization\");\n  if (!auth?.startsWith(\"Bearer \")) return null;\n  const decoded = verifyJwt(auth.substring(7));\n  if (!decoded?.email) return null;\n  const user = (API_MOCK_USERS as Record<string, MockUserDbEntry>)[decoded.email.toLowerCase().trim()];\n  return user && user.status !== \"inactive\" ? user : null;\n}\n\nexport async function PATCH(req: Request, { params }: { params: any }) {\n  try {\n    const caller = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (!caller) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Unauthorized\" }, { status: 401 });\n    const { id } = await params;\n    const ticket = (API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS as Record<string, ApiSupportTicket>)[id];\n    if (!ticket) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Not Found\" }, { status: 404 });\n\n    const isAdmin = caller.role === \"gff_admin\";\n    if (!isAdmin) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Only administrators can assign tickets.\" }, { status: 403 });\n    }\n\n    const b = await req.json().catch(() => null);\n    if (!b || (b.assigned_to !== null && typeof b.assigned_to !== \"string\")) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid assigned_to value.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    ticket.assigned_to = b.assigned_to ? b.assigned_to.trim() : null;\n    ticket.lastUpdated = new Date().toISOString();\n    (API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS as Record<string, ApiSupportTicket>)[id] = ticket;\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, ticket });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n"}}}
