{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:54:15.874Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining the Endpoint**\n\nI'm currently focused on defining the final API endpoint for comments within the support system. Specifically, I'm fleshing out the structure for `/api/v1/support/[id]/comments`, considering that it needs to handle POST requests. I'm now thinking about what data the POST request should accept, settling on a `{ text: \"comment body\" }` structure for the request body.\n\n\n**Refining the Input Structure**\n\nI've considered other structures for the request body, such as `{ comment: \"comment body\" }` or `{ reply: \"comment body\" }`, and I'm leaning toward `{ reply: \"comment body\" }`. This fits nicely with the `ticket.replies` structure. I'm now drafting the `/api/v1/support/[id]/comments/route.ts` file, aiming to handle both formats robustly.\n\n\n**Implementing Error Handling**\n\nI've just added error handling to the `/api/v1/support/[id]/comments` route. I'm focusing on crafting specific, informative responses for different error scenarios, such as unauthorized access, not found tickets, invalid JSON, and empty comment text, making sure each response has the right HTTP status code. I'm refining the response structure now for different error conditions.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:54:15.876Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"26bau2kf","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/api/v1/support/[id]/comments/route.ts","new_text":"import { NextResponse } from \"next/server\";\nimport { \n  API_MOCK_USERS, API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS, verifyJwt, \n  MockUserDbEntry, ApiSupportTicket, getClientIdFromAssociation \n} from \"@/lib/api-auth\";\n\nexport const runtime = \"nodejs\";\n\nfunction getAuthCaller(req: Request) {\n  const auth = req.headers.get(\"authorization\");\n  if (!auth?.startsWith(\"Bearer \")) return null;\n  const decoded = verifyJwt(auth.substring(7));\n  if (!decoded?.email) return null;\n  const user = (API_MOCK_USERS as Record<string, MockUserDbEntry>)[decoded.email.toLowerCase().trim()];\n  return user && user.status !== \"inactive\" ? user : null;\n}\n\nexport async function POST(req: Request, { params }: { params: any }) {\n  try {\n    const caller = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (!caller) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Unauthorized\" }, { status: 401 });\n    const { id } = await params;\n    const ticket = (API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS as Record<string, ApiSupportTicket>)[id];\n    if (!ticket) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Not Found\" }, { status: 404 });\n\n    const isAdmin = caller.role === \"gff_admin\";\n    if (!isAdmin && ticket.client_id !== getClientIdFromAssociation(caller.clientAssociation)) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Access denied.\" }, { status: 403 });\n    }\n\n    const b = await req.json().catch(() => null);\n    if (!b) return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid JSON\" }, { status: 400 });\n\n    const text = b.text || b.comment || b.reply;\n    if (!text || typeof text !== \"string\" || !text.trim()) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid or empty comment text.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const newComment = {\n      id: `rep-${Math.floor(1000 + Math.random() * 9000)}`,\n      sender: isAdmin ? `${caller.name} (Admin)` : caller.name,\n      text: text.trim(),\n      timestamp: new Date().toISOString()\n    };\n\n    ticket.replies.push(newComment);\n    ticket.lastUpdated = new Date().toISOString();\n    (API_MOCK_SUPPORT_TICKETS as Record<string, ApiSupportTicket>)[id] = ticket;\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, ticket, comment: newComment });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n"}}}
