{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:55:27.036Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"kv8ziq2i","input":{"summary":"We successfully designed, implemented, and verified the MVP Support Ticket CRUD APIs under /api/v1/support.\n\nSummary of Changes:\n1. `lib/api-auth.ts`: Added typescript models (ApiSupportTicket, ApiSupportTicketComment), a deterministic dataset of mock support tickets that perfectly maps to the existing frontend, globally persisted in-memory mock database hookups matching existing API structures, and a secure ID generator.\n2. `app/api/v1/support/route.ts`: Implemented support ticket list retrieval with fully validated filters (status, priority, category, client_id, project_id, assigned_to, search) and support ticket creation. RBAC is enforced, ensuring client roles can only access and create tickets within their respective client boundaries.\n3. `app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.ts`: Implemented get ticket by ID (GET) and general ticket updates (PATCH). Updates accept general fields (title, description, category, priority), status changes, assigned_to assignments, or appending comments/replies.\n4. `app/api/v1/support/[id]/status/route.ts`: Exposed a dedicated sub-endpoint to update a ticket's status.\n5. `app/api/v1/support/[id]/assign/route.ts`: Exposed a dedicated sub-endpoint to assign a ticket (restricted to administrators).\n6. `app/api/v1/support/[id]/comments/route.ts`: Exposed a dedicated sub-endpoint to append comments/replies to a ticket under secure tenant boundaries.\n\nVerification Done:\n- Run 'npx tsc --noEmit' and compiled with zero errors.\n- Run 'npx eslint app/api/v1/support' and linted with zero errors.\n- Ran 'npm run verify-tools' which passed with 100% success (all 25 deterministic checks passed).\n- Ensured strict compliance with UI Quality Constitution, workspace guardrails, and Next.js 16 requirements.","verified":true}}}
